    "seriesContrast": "Ghibli Pastel L0.80/C0.11 is a defining stylistic identity of OsakaNights and is used identically in Day and Night. Categorical marks are always legended (colour-never-alone) and clear CVD adjacency (worst ΔE 9.3), so the sub-3:1 mark contrast on the light plot surface is an accepted, deliberate trade for this theme. Do not darken the palette or the chart bed to satisfy the gate."
